frameDefinitions: A Payer gives up (or potentially gives up) the use of an Asset (generally money) in order to achieve an Intended_event.
An Assailant physically attacks a Victim (which is usually but not always sentient), causing or intending to cause the Victim physical damage.
In this frame, an Agent engages in personal body care by grooming either a Patient or a Body_part.
An Agent brings about the end of a Theme's captivity at a Location_of_confinement in contravention of the plans or desires of a captor.

A less-powerful person or group of people (the Activists) engages in an activity aimed to inconvenience or weaken a more powerful person or group (the Institution) to seek redress, in the form of a series of Demands, for the wrondgoings committed by the Instituion.  '
The words in this frame refer to what Clothing the Wearer (or a specific Body_part of the Wearer) has on.
frameExamples: It 'll <t>cost</t> Sandra's parents fifty grand a year for her to attend that school.
As soon as he stepped out of the bar he was <t>set</t> upon by four men in ski-masks.
His accomplice <t>freed</t> him from Sing Sing prison thanks to his disguise.
The workers were <t>striking</t> for better wages and better benefits.
I <t>had</t> <t>on</t> the most ridiculous monkey-suit you could imagine.
listRoleDefinitions: The role <fen>Goods</fen> is the item(s) whose price is being assessed.  <fen>Goods</fen> is usually an External Argument:
The person whose <fen>Asset</fen> is given up in order to achieve an <fen>Intended_event</fen>.  This role is often expressed as INI.
The price of or payment made for the Goods.
The event that the <fen>Payer</fen> brings about by deploying the <fen>Asset</fen>.
The time when a transaction takes place.
This role is the being or entity that is injured by the <fen>Assailant</fen>'s attack.
The person (or other self-directed entity) that is attempting physical harm to the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Assailant</fen> attacks the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Assailant</fen> makes an assault on the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The agent is the person who does the grooming.
The patient is the person who gets washed.
This is the region of the body that gets groomed.
This role identifies the time when the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the individual who ends the confinement or captivity of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the person or object in motion released by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The location to which the <fen>Theme</fen>'s motion was formerly inhibited.
The <fen>Time</fen> identifies when the <fen>Agent</fen> release the <fen>Theme</fen> .
The location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ceases to be confined.
The person or group of people that act out against the <fen>Institution</fen> in an attempt to have their <fen>Demands</fen> fullfilled.
The <fen>Institution</fen> is the company, factory, political party / institution, or entity that yields authority over the <fen>Activists</fen>.

The <fen>Demands</fen> are the guarantee(s) given by the <fen>Institution</fen> to the <fen>Activists</fen> that act to correct or address the issues or state of affairs that were grievous to the <fen>Activists</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the location where the political action occurs.
The person whose clothing is under discussion.
This role identifies the <fen>Clothing</fen> that the <fen>Wearer</fen> wears.
The body part of the <fen>Wearer</fen> which is covered by the <fen>Clothing</fen>.
The time at or during which the <fen>Wearer</fen> has the <fen>Clothing</fen> on.
